FedEx results mixed, financial outlook for 2016 lowered
FedEx reported disappointing results for the latest quarter, and the delivery giant lowered its full-year profit outlook because of weaker demand for freight services and higher costs in its ground transportation service.
The company also said it plans to hire about 55,000 seasonal workers for the holidays.
At this time last year, FedEx announced plans to hire 50,000 seasonal workers for the holiday season.
The stock fell more than 2.5 percent in premarket trading 45 minutes before the open on Wednesday.
FedEx Corp said it expects to earn a profit of between $10.40 and $10.90 in the fiscal year ending next May, down 20 cents from its earlier forecast.
