Police arrested a man after a collision with a cyclist and subsequent hit-and-run in Cobram over the weekend.
The cyclist was taken by helicopter to the Royal Melbourne Hospital with serious injuries after being struck by a car on the Murray Valley Highway on Saturday morning.
Police said the motorist drove on without stopping to help the injured driver.
On Monday, a 50-year-old Nathalia man turned himself in to police in Shepparton.
