The girl was interviewed and said the accused used computers and Playstation to talk to girls who looked much younger than him.
Hogg, 23, Ward Road, Dundee, pleaded guilty to the charges of taking indecent images of children on June 14 last year, breaching conditions on January 25 this year and failing to appear in court for a hearing on March 24 this year.
Defence lawyer Gregor Sim asked that Hogg not appear on the register of sexual offenders, arguing that there was "no significant sexual element" to his offence.
